I downloaded software from the Ecofont website and compared the print out with printing in grayscale. The ecofont print (i printed in the arial font) looked sharper compared to the grayscale output. When you put it under the magnifyer i noticed the holes in the ecofont print out varies in diameter and are exactly in the middle of the letter. In grayscale there were many little holes at a fixed distance. As a result the outline of the letter is not intact. I guess that makes the difference. &lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
BTW I was supprised to see it works with normal fonts, I did not had to install the ecofont with holes.&lt;br /&gt;

